to go and see my dad?

257
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:55,720
This is probably the first disagreement we've had since we started dating.

258
00:22:57,890 --> 00:23:00,050
When you were ignoring me,

259
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:02,330
I really didn't know what to do.

260
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:06,790
All right. I won't ever be like that in the future again.

261
00:23:11,910 --> 00:23:13,950
Do you want to watch a series?

262
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:21,720
Well... will you watch the first episode

263
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,620
of "Tu Bo Tu" with me?

264
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:29,560
I'll watch whatever you want with you.

265
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:35,490
You said that this will be pretty hard, right?

266
00:23:35,490 --> 00:23:37,610
Aren't you two professionals?

267
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:39,710
Yes, please listen to me.

268
00:23:39,710 --> 00:23:43,260
If both parties reach a consensus, then there will be no issues, of course.

269
00:23:43,260 --> 00:23:45,720
But right now, the only reasoning that we have is yours, which is that you no longer love your husband.

270
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:48,480
And there is no way that alone will constitute a sufficient element for divorce.

271
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:52,320
Therefore, I must have one of those reasons that you stated before, is that right?

272
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:55,020
It is not possible to unilaterally petition for divorce,

273
00:23:55,020 --> 00:23:57,150
unless your cause meets one of the ten statutory reasons.

274
00:23:57,150 --> 00:24:00,150
If you want to get a divorce for a reason such as incompatible personalities, it is truly impossible.

275
00:24:00,150 --> 00:24:03,290
And what if I must get a divorce?

276
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:14,240
Mrs. Wang, I apologize. I believe this is the most direct way of dealing with this.

277
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,330
Sit, please.

278
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:25,870
Hello, I'm the lawyer that will be responsible for this matter this time. My surname is Zheng.

279
00:24:25,870 --> 00:24:29,200
I'm aware. Lawyer Fu just gave me an introduction.

280
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:36,910
So, you really found a lawyer to take care of this?

281
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:39,170
I originally thought I wasn't going to sign the papers and that we didn't need a divorce.

282
00:24:39,170 --> 00:24:43,960
Actually, this is how things are. But do you really think this is a good method?

283
00:24:58,230 --> 00:25:03,010
I apologize. May I trouble you to take care of this matter for us? Thank you.

284
00:25:05,460 --> 00:25:07,760
All right. I will draw up an agreement here.

285
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,290
There's no need for that.

286
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:17,230
I always carry it around with me.

287
00:25:44,910 --> 00:25:47,220
Are you still thinking about today's case?

288
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:56,190
He let her go for the sake of helping her achieve what she wanted, and they're separated now.

289
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:01,810
It's hard to imagine, how determined that man was.

290
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:10,530
Perhaps it was because he felt the determination and resoluteness of his wife.

291
00:26:10,530 --> 00:26:15,720
And because he loves her, he, therefore, decided to let her go, and rather bring that pain upon himself.

292
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,670
Do you think that woman is very selfish, then?

293
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:35,840
Regardless of their separation,

294
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:39,060
when it comes to emotional choices, who isn't selfish?

295
00:26:39,060 --> 00:26:41,640
You just can't cause yourself to have any regrets.

296
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:51,160
I'll always be by your side.

297
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:53,390
Let's go and see your dad.

298
00:27:07,450 --> 00:27:09,770
- Do you have everything?
- Dad.

299
00:27:09,770 --> 00:27:11,220
Mr. Zheng.

300
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:15,360
What... are you two doing here?

301
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:18,290
I just happened to be going to the hospital. We can talk about it afterward.

302
00:27:18,290 --> 00:27:21,780
Fu Ligong and I are here, why are you avoiding us?

303
00:27:23,390 --> 00:27:27,790
Dad, same-sex marriage has passed now. Don't be so old-fashioned and inflexible.

304
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:31,190
What is going on right now?

305
00:27:31,190 --> 00:27:33,600
I'm the bad guy, right?

306
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,570
Mr. Zheng, that's not how I feel.

307
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:38,340
Little Gong, I know that's not what you mean.

308
00:27:38,910 --> 00:27:41,150
Little Gong, you've always been a good kid.

309
00:27:41,150 --> 00:27:44,680
Don't you know what I'm thinking?

310
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,270
So, let me ask you.

311
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:49,460
What do you want to talk about with me?

312
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:57,050
He and I are going to see Uncle Wang together.

313
00:27:57,050 --> 00:28:00,760
We're going to go and chat with him, just like how he insisted that I come here and talk with you.

314
00:28:04,580 --> 00:28:06,480
What on Earth do you two want to talk about with me?

315
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:08,180
We've already thought it over.

316
00:28:08,180 --> 00:28:10,700
Regardless of what happens,

317
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:13,030
we're going to face it together.

318
00:28:13,030 --> 00:28:15,110
Please understand us.

319
00:28:17,650 --> 00:28:20,940
Mr. Zheng, I promise you.

320
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:25,170
I will always be with Zeshou.

321
00:28:46,110 --> 00:28:47,740
What is this?

322
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:49,930
It's a letter to you, from your mom.

323
00:28:51,050 --> 00:28:54,160
Your mother is already in a coma now.

324
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:57,180
She knew that she wouldn't have a way to speak with you again.

325
00:28:57,180 --> 00:28:59,090
Everything that she wanted to tell you before she fell into a coma,

326
00:28:59,090 --> 00:29:02,270
is in this letter.

327
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:08,040
You must remember. You have a mother that loves you very much.

328
00:29:24,890 --> 00:29:26,950
Lock the door when you leave.

329
00:29:37,230 --> 00:29:40,750
Zeshou, I'm sorry.

330
00:29:40,750 --> 00:29:43,880
At that time, when I willfully left you...

331
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:47,440
Actually, I felt regret very quickly thereafter.

332
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,650
I shouldn't have only thought of myself.

333
00:29:49,650 --> 00:29:53,710
I caused you and Xueqing to have a broken family from a small age.

334
00:29:53,710 --> 00:29:55,680
However, I didn't dare to return.

335
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:58,830
I was afraid that you two wouldn't willingly accept me.

336
00:29:58,830 --> 00:30:00,300
After you all moved,

337
00:30:00,300 --> 00:30:03,000
I continued and always lived in our old neighborhood.

338
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,460
And I secretly watched you and Xueqing grow up.

339
00:30:05,460 --> 00:30:10,590
I even imagined returning to your sides, and living with you again.

340
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:14,060
Even though I knew that I had no right to see you two,

341
00:30:14,060 --> 00:30:18,210
I still hoped that you would be able to establish your own happy families.

342
00:30:18,210 --> 00:30:22,630
And live a simple and happy life.

343
00:30:22,630 --> 00:30:26,990
Zeshou, I'm not a good mother.

344
00:30:26,990 --> 00:30:29,090
You don't have to forgive me,

345
00:30:29,090 --> 00:30:31,520
but you must always be happy.

346
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,410
Why?

347
00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:13,110
Why does she get to arbitrarily decide what's good for us?

348
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:15,830
Why does she think she knows what kind of life we should lead?

349
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:19,140
Why didn't she try, even

350
00:31:19,140 --> 00:31:21,640
one time, to see us when she was healthy?

351
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:24,490
Why did she have to wait until she was seriously ill and about to die?

352
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:33,040
And why does this suddenly make me feel like I'm the one who's done something wrong?

353
00:31:57,310 --> 00:31:59,340
You haven't done anything wrong.

354
00:32:02,030 --> 00:32:05,910
Perhaps... your mother had a reason that she didn't dare to share with you.

355
00:32:20,510 --> 00:32:24,490
Don't worry, I'll always be by your side.

356
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:37,280
I'm fine.

357
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:42,850
Okay, I'm going to go take a shower.

358
00:33:27,210 --> 00:33:32,380
♫ This feeling... I'm still infatuated ♫

359
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:37,530
♫ A line that can't be crossed ♫

360
00:33:37,530 --> 00:33:42,630
♫ That moment... of touching ♫

361
00:33:42,630 --> 00:33:47,290
♫ Only exists between positive and negative ♫

362
00:33:47,290 --> 00:33:52,650
♫ I love you... ♫

363
00:33:52,650 --> 00:33:57,600
♫ I miss you... ♫

364
00:33:57,600 --> 00:34:03,110
♫ The lies are stuck in my heart inch by inch ♫

365
00:34:03,110 --> 00:34:07,710
♫ Carved in my bones and engraved in my heart,
I long to see you again ♫

366
00:34:07,710 --> 00:34:12,820
♫ My longing for you still resides in that room ♫

367
00:34:12,820 --> 00:34:18,150
♫ I want to hold you again, to hold you tighter ♫

368
00:34:18,150 --> 00:34:23,120
♫ The phrase "I love you" is still on the right side of the bed ♫

369
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:28,640
♫ I wish you could feel how I feel ♫

370
00:34:30,140 --> 00:34:33,070
Fu Ligong!

371
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:36,820
Thank you for liking me!
